# Open Composer OOD embed — dashboard environment overrides (example)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy the lines you need into the OOD dashboard's env file:
#
#     /etc/ood/config/apps/dashboard/env
#
# then restart the web server (Help -> Restart Web Server, or
# `sudo systemctl reload httpd`). All variables are OPTIONAL — the defaults
# work for a standard single-host OOD that serves HTTPS on port 443 with
# Open Composer installed as the sys app "opencomposer".

# --- Which sys app to embed -------------------------------------------------
# The Open Composer sys-app directory name — the "<name>" in /pun/sys/<name>.
# This must match the directory under /var/www/ood/apps/sys/ (NOT the tile's
# display name). Examples: "opencomposer", "OpenComposer", "slurm_composer".
# Default: opencomposer
#
# OC_EMBED_APP_NAME=slurm_composer

# --- Where the proxy reaches OOD's Apache (the upstream call) ----------------
# The embed makes a server-side request back to OOD's portal vhost to fetch
# Open Composer, forwarding the user's session cookie. By default it connects
# to the loopback IP 127.0.0.1 but uses the SAME host/port/scheme the browser
# used for TLS SNI and the Host header — correct for a standard host serving
# HTTPS on 443 (including hosts with several name-based vhosts).
#
# Override these ONLY if your front end differs — e.g. a TLS-terminating load
# balancer where the portal vhost actually listens on a plain-HTTP port, or
# Apache is bound to a specific address.
#
#   OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_HOST    Hostname used for TLS SNI + the Host header.
#                             Default: the host from the incoming request.
#   OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_PORT    Port to connect to. Default: the request's port.
#   OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_SCHEME  http or https. Default: the request's scheme.
#   OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_IP      IP to actually connect to (TCP), independent of
#                             the SNI host above. Default: 127.0.0.1.
#                             Set empty to resolve OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_HOST via DNS
#                             instead of forcing loopback.
#
# Example — OOD behind a load balancer, portal vhost on local HTTP port 8080:
#
# OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_HOST=ondemand.example.org
# OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_PORT=8080
# OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_SCHEME=http
# OC_EMBED_UPSTREAM_IP=127.0.0.1
